---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <Fragment slot="title">About</Fragment>

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-10">
    About
  </h1>

  <div class="space-y-8 text-muted leading-8">
    <p>
      I come from Hyderabad, a city deeply connected to technology and innovation.
      Growing up with both of my parents working as software engineers, I was
      constantly surrounded by conversations about systems, problem solving, and
      how software quietly powers the world around us. Technology never felt distant
      to me. It felt natural.
    </p>

    <p>
      As a child, I was captivated by the idea of building things that felt almost
      futuristic. Watching Tony Stark design and construct advanced technology in
      Iron Man did not just entertain me. It sparked something deeper. I was fascinated
      by the process of creation, by the idea that intelligence and engineering could
      turn imagination into reality. That emotion never really left me.
    </p>

    <p>
      That curiosity matured into a desire to understand how real systems work.
      I pursued Computer Science not just as a degree, but as a way to explore
      how software is architected, how it scales, and how it impacts people.
      Today, I focus on backend engineering and infrastructure, working with
      FastAPI, PostgreSQL, and Docker to build reliable and scalable systems.
    </p>

    <p>
      My interest in open source became a natural extension of that curiosity.
      I actively contribute to open source projects and am part of one of the
      leading open source clubs in India - amFOSS. Being involved in
      this ecosystem has shaped how I think about collaboration, code quality,
      and long term system design. It has also given me the opportunity to mentor,
      review code, and help build sustainable technical communities.
    </p>

    <p>
      I do not like restricting myself to a single domain. Exploring backend
      systems, infrastructure, distributed architectures, and emerging areas
      like agent based AI systems allows me to constantly grow. For me, building
      software is not just about shipping features. It is about constructing
      systems that are thoughtful, resilient, and meaningful.
    </p>

    <p>
      One day, I hope to build technology ambitious enough to feel like something
      out of science fiction. Not fantasy, but engineering driven innovation.
      The kind of systems that once inspired me on screen, but built in reality.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>